quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  18,45,"Cite for them the parable of the life of this world, it is like water that We send down from the sky and is absorbed by the plants of the earth. But in time it becomes dry chaff, scattered by the winds. And it is God who has absolute power over all things"
  18,46,"Wealth and children are adornments of this worldly life, but the enduring good deeds produce a greater reward from your Lord and a better hope"
  18,47,"On the Day We will set the mountains in motion, and you see the earth emerging, and We will gather them all, leaving not a single one behind"
  18,48,"They will be lined up before your Lord, [and He will say] \"You have come to Us just as We created you in the first instance. Even though you claimed that We will not make such an appointment for you"
  18,49,"And the Book [of deeds] will be laid [open], and you will see those who forced others to reject God's messages filled with dread at what is in it, and they will say, \"Alas for us! What a record is this! It leaves out no deeds, small or great, but accounts for it!\" They will find everything they ever did present [before them]. Your Lord will not be unjust to anyone"